%N A394427 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} ((1-1/p)^2 * Sum_{k>=0} (k^2+1)/p^(k^2)).
%C A394427 The asymptotic probability that the product of two positive integers selected independently at random is a number whose prime factorization exponents are all squares (A197680).
%e A394427 0.349622561337888279499195419864524551535567669131557...
%o A394427 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((1-1/p)^2 * sum(k=0,m,(k^2+1)/p^(k^2)));
%o A394427 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
